snippet: Prosecutors on Monday tried to prove one of the gravest charges against Pfc. Bradley Manning: that the Army private, who gave WikiLeaks diplomatic and military documents, aided Al Qaeda.
abstract: Prosecutors in case against Pfc Bradley Manning try to prove that he aided Al Qaeda by giving diplomatic and military documents to WikiLeaks.
lead_paragraph: Prosecutors on Monday tried to prove one of the gravest charges against Pfc. Bradley Manning: that the Army private, who gave WikiLeaks diplomatic and military documents, aided Al Qaeda.

headline.main: Maryland: Al Qaeda Used WikiLeaks, Prosecutors Say
headline.print_headline: Maryland: Al Qaeda Used Wikileaks, Prosecutors Say
